results.definition: gymnastic apparatus consisting of a pair of heavy metal circles (usually covered with leather) suspended by ropes; used for gymnastic exercises
examples: the rings require a strong upper body
it has the ring of sincerity
a ring of ships in the harbor
a halo of smoke

results.definition: a rigid circular band of metal or wood or other material used for holding or fastening or hanging or pulling
examples: there was still a rusty iron hoop for tying a horse

results.definition: (chemistry) a chain of atoms in a molecule that forms a closed loop

examples: police tried to break up the gang
a pack of thieves

results.definition: the sound of a bell ringing
examples: the distinctive ring of the church bell
the ringing of the telephone
the tintinnabulation that so voluminously swells from the ringing and the dinging of the bells"--E. A. Poe

results.definition: a platform usually marked off by ropes in which contestants box or wrestle
jewelry consisting of a circlet of precious metal (often set with jewels) worn on the finger
examples: she had rings on every finger
he noted that she wore a wedding band

results.definition: a strip of material attached to the leg of a bird to identify it (as in studies of bird migration)

examples: the bells rang
the hall resounded with laughter

results.definition: make (bells) ring, often for the purposes of musical edification
examples: Ring the bells
My uncle rings every Sunday at the local church

results.definition: get or try to get into communication (with someone) by telephone
examples: I tried to call you all night
Take two aspirin and call me in the morning

results.definition: extend on all sides of simultaneously; encircle
examples: The forest surrounds my property

results.definition: attach a ring to the foot of, in order to identify
examples: ring birds
band the geese to observe their migratory patterns
